				 Herculis moving stellar groups.

Much work in searching for and analyzing moving stellar groups was
done at the time by O. Eggen. For example, he described the Sirius
kinematic group (Eggen 1960). Agekyan and Orlov (1984) analyzed
several moving stellar groups based on data from the Catalog of
Nearby Stars (Glieze 1969). The star


						\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
