				 Pictoris
(Glieze 1969) turned out to be a member of even two groups.

The Hipparcos (1997) catalogue exerted a revolutionary influence on the search
for and analysis of moving stellar groups. For example, beginning with the
papers of Barrado y NavascuÃ©s et al. (1999) and Zuckerman et al. (2001) based
on Hipparcos data, the


						\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
