				 Pictoris moving group. For this purpose, we use data from
the Gaia DR3 catalog (Vallenari et al. 2023). The sample is based
on exclusively single stars, according to the classification of
Lee et al. (2024). The method consists in tracing back the orbits
of stars on a given time interval and estimating the time when the
stellar group had a minimum spatial size.

